<div class="schema-faq wp-block-yoast-faq-block"><div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1623393125914"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Can overweight people start calisthenics?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Yes, calisthenics is accessible for all body types. It offers joint-friendly exercises that can be modified for individual needs and abilities.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1733306295794"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Can you start calisthenics at any weight?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Yes, anyone can start calisthenics at any weight. By adjusting angles or using support props, you can modify intensity and ensure exercises are adaptable to your needs. This makes calisthenics suitable for individuals of all fitness levels and body types.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1733306296465"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Can you lose body fat with calisthenics?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Yes, you can lose body fat with calisthenics when paired with a balanced diet. Calisthenics combines strength training and movement which <a href="https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Ali-Erdem-Cigerci/publication/342339065_The_Effect_of_Calisthenics_Exercises_on_Body_Composition_in_Soccer_Players/links/5eee7aff299bf1faac68c131/The-Effect-of-Calisthenics-Exercises-on-Body-Composition-in-Soccer-Players.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">reduces fat percentage and improves lean mass</a>.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1733306297133"><strong class="schema-faq-question">What exercises should overweight people avoid?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Avoid high-impact movements like jump squats or burpees initially. Focus on low-impact options, progressing as your strength and endurance improve.</p> </div> </div>
